[show NS]Partner's decline was the honest answer to your question, and passing it out was right: on a bare 32 you invite and abide by partner's verdict rather than guessing. As the cards lay, 6NT would have rolled in, and eleven tricks came home at 4NT, but do not let a single lucky layout rewrite the method. Bid 4NT as an invitation, respect the reply, and over many hands trusting partner's count beats forcing to slam on a hopeful 32.}
